<subSubSection id="C3376516FFE99212FF642E12FCB463CD" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFE99212FF642E12FEF6625A" blockId="1.[151,274,1565,1591]" box="[151,274,1565,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<heading id="D0DA81F1FFE99212FF642E12FEF6625A" bold="true" box="[151,274,1565,1591]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FF642E12FEF6625A" bold="true" box="[151,274,1565,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFE99212FF642E69FCB463CD" blockId="1.[151,1436,1638,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
Among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FEED2E69FE6C62ED" authorityName="Laicharting" authorityYear="1781" box="[286,392,1638,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Gryllinae">Gryllinae</taxonomicName>
genera, this new genus described here is average sized with a black coloration. It possesses tympana on outside tibia and well developed forewing with mirror. Two filiform hairs on foretibia are its unique feature. General appearance is close to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FD682EA1FCF562A5" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1992" box="[667,785,1710,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Vietacheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FD682EA1FCF562A5" box="[667,785,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Vietacheta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the ectoparamere of the new genus is little wider than the lateral lobes of epiphallus in lateral view, while the ectoparamere of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FC4B2EDDFBCA6281" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1992" box="[952,1070,1746,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Vietacheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FC4B2EDDFBCA6281" box="[952,1070,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Vietacheta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is covered by the lateral lobes of epiphallus. The genitalia are also similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FD222EF9FCBD637D" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1983" box="[721,857,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Phonarellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FD222EF9FCBD637D" box="[721,857,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Phonarellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the epiphallus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FBA72EF9FB38637D" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1983" box="[1108,1244,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Phonarellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FBA72EF9FB38637D" box="[1108,1244,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Phonarellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not possess notch in middle. Compared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FDFA2F15FD4C6359" box="[521,680,1818,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Gymnogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FDFA2F15FD4C6359" box="[521,680,1818,1844]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Gymnogryllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the new genus is smaller in size. Furthermore, the ectoparamere of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FF642F31FED26335" box="[151,310,1854,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Gymnogryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FF642F31FED26335" box="[151,310,1854,1880]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Gymnogryllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer, while that of the new genus is shorter than the lateral lobe of epiphallus. Its genitalia are also similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FE552F6DFDA06311" authorityName="Gorochov" authorityYear="1992" box="[422,580,1890,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Apterosvercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FE552F6DFDA06311" box="[422,580,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Apterosvercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while the latter has no tympana or wings. Molecular results supported the validation of the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFE99212FE272F89FD9A63CD" authority="He" authorityName="He" authorityYear="2022" box="[468,638,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Fodigryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FE272F89FDB363CD" box="[468,599,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Fodigryllus</emphasis>
He
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFE99212FD762F89FD0A63CD" bold="true" box="[645,750,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26A57F4FFE99212FD762F89FD0A63CD" box="[645,750,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A18FFE99212FD0E2F89FCDB63CD" box="[765,831,1926,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1109,1133]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,201,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[264,1323,201,1085]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. The phylogenetic relationship inferred from the COI concatenated fragments. The tree was rooted by Velarifictorus arisanicus and constructed by Maximum likelihood (ML) with TIM2+I+G4+F model. Topology supports of all major nodes are indicated above branches by SH-aLRT value and the bootstrap value." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457449/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3376516FFEA9211FF642898FDE664DC" box="[151,514,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" type="description">
