</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF526615FFEA9211FF642C5AFCB260DE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457449" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6457449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" startId="2.[151,250,1109,1133]" targetBox="[264,1323,201,1079]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEA9211FF642C5AFCB260DE" blockId="2.[151,1436,1109,1203]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEA9211FF642C5AFEF66000" bold="true" box="[151,274,1109,1133]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
The phylogenetic relationship inferred from the 
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEA9211FD082C59FCC36000" box="[763,807,1110,1133]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">COI</emphasis>
concatenated fragments. The tree was rooted by 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D1EFFEA9211FAE12C5AFEE560FD" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1930" baseAuthorityName="Shiraki" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arisanicus">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEA9211FAE12C5AFEE560FD" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">Velarifictorus arisanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and constructed by Maximum likelihood (ML) with TIM2+I+G4+F model. Topology supports of all major nodes are indicated above branches by SH-aLRT value and the bootstrap value.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3376516FFEA9211FF642CD1FAB26095" box="[151,1366,1246,1273]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B92369DFFEA9211FF642CD1FAB26095" blockId="2.[151,1366,1246,1273]" box="[151,1366,1246,1273]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis id="B959EA8FFFEA9211FF642CD1FEFA6095" bold="true" box="[151,286,1246,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is derived from Latin Fodi- (dig) + gryllus, which refers to its burrowing habit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
